WEBVTT

00:04.770 --> 00:06.761
*

00:10.810 --> 00:12.539
If I die before you,

00:12.580 --> 00:14.605
please don't let them read
"Wind Beneath My Wings"

00:14.640 --> 00:16.505
at my funeral.

00:16.550 --> 00:19.542
Who knew it had
so many verses?

00:19.580 --> 00:21.013
(both chuckle)

00:25.290 --> 00:27.383
You think
that we didn't know him

00:27.420 --> 00:29.729
or his family didn't?

00:29.760 --> 00:32.228
Maybe he changed.

00:32.260 --> 00:35.058
They said he liked
nighttime walks in the snow?

00:35.100 --> 00:36.624
He hated the snow.

00:36.670 --> 00:38.092
(both snicker)

00:38.130 --> 00:40.189
What about that food?

00:40.240 --> 00:41.639
I didn't know he cooked.

00:41.670 --> 00:44.138
He didn't!
They're crazy.

00:44.170 --> 00:46.309
(both laugh)

00:46.340 --> 00:48.399
I need another drink.

00:50.580 --> 00:54.209
We were like
the two mistresses
at the Irish funeral.

00:54.250 --> 00:56.810
Yep.

00:56.850 --> 01:00.354
Oh, I'm sorry.
I meant that metaphorically.

01:00.390 --> 01:01.584
I know.

01:01.620 --> 01:04.657
(laughs)

01:06.300 --> 01:07.597
Thank you.

01:10.130 --> 01:11.427
(clears throat)

01:12.840 --> 01:14.796
To Will.

01:14.840 --> 01:17.104
To Will,
a real man.

01:18.410 --> 01:20.298
He shall be missed.

01:25.410 --> 01:28.277
DIANE:
My dad was a sloppy drunk.

01:28.320 --> 01:31.187
I said I'd never be like him.
(snorts)

01:31.220 --> 01:33.279
You're not sloppy.

01:33.320 --> 01:35.515
You're elegant.

01:35.560 --> 01:39.121
Mm, I always wanted
to be like you.

01:39.160 --> 01:41.355
No.
No, I did.

01:41.400 --> 01:44.289
When I came to
Lockhart/Gardner,

01:44.330 --> 01:49.165
the way you... held yourself.

01:49.210 --> 01:51.861
I was a great disappointment
to my mother.

01:51.910 --> 01:54.777
She wanted me to be a nurse.

01:54.810 --> 01:58.143
Get married, have three kids.

01:58.180 --> 01:59.317
Be a nurse.

01:59.350 --> 02:00.647
My mom thinks
I'm a prude.

02:00.680 --> 02:02.511
(laughs)

02:02.550 --> 02:08.216
I know. She thinks
I should loosen up

02:08.260 --> 02:10.683
and get laid more.

02:10.730 --> 02:12.857
(phone rings)
Oh, no.

02:12.900 --> 02:15.357
Oh, let me guess.

02:15.400 --> 02:18.369
Yep, it's David Lee.

02:18.400 --> 02:19.936
Hey, let me answer.

02:19.970 --> 02:22.268
It'll terrify him.

02:22.310 --> 02:24.437
Come on. He'll think _
we're merging or something.

02:24.470 --> 02:25.767
Come on.

02:25.810 --> 02:27.778
(phone beeps)
(laughs)

02:27.810 --> 02:30.506
I'm so alone there.

02:30.550 --> 02:35.772
Partners look at me like
I'm a gazelle on the savanna.

02:35.820 --> 02:37.811
They always looked
at you like that.

02:37.850 --> 02:40.216
No, this is different.

02:40.260 --> 02:43.229
Will was on a buying binge.

02:43.260 --> 02:44.921
Now we're overextended.

02:44.960 --> 02:46.894
Yeah, we are, too.

02:49.000 --> 02:50.695
Well, we should merge.

02:52.840 --> 02:53.966
What?

02:54.000 --> 02:55.763
We should merge our firms.

02:55.800 --> 02:58.462
How would we do that?

02:58.510 --> 03:00.432
By saying we will.

03:00.480 --> 03:02.402
You would want that?

03:02.450 --> 03:03.439
Well, I would want
Chumhum back.

03:03.480 --> 03:06.711
That would_ solve a lot
of my Issues.

03:06.750 --> 03:08.615
You'd take Chumhum and
(clicks tongue)

03:08.650 --> 03:10.242
get rid of us.

03:10.290 --> 03:12.417
No. We'd draw up
a contract.

03:12.460 --> 03:15.349
I have to have someone
to take WIll's place anyway.

03:15.390 --> 03:18.848
Our firms are fighting
on a lot of fronts.

03:18.890 --> 03:21.450
Oh, and your client is divorcing
our client.

03:21.500 --> 03:23.559
No, your client
is divorcing ours.

03:23.600 --> 03:27.229
(chuckles)

03:27.270 --> 03:30.398
Well, so, let's keep talking.

03:30.440 --> 03:32.635
We'll make peace and...

03:32.680 --> 03:34.807
Come on. We'll figure out
how to make this work.

03:39.550 --> 03:40.972
(elevator bell dings)

03:41.020 --> 03:43.716
CARY:
Your husband's divorce lavwer's
named David Lee.

03:43.750 --> 03:46.480
He can be very contentious,
so don't get thrown by anything.

03:46.520 --> 03:47.885
I don't get thrown
by anything anymore.

03:47.920 --> 03:49.387
We have leverage.

03:49.430 --> 03:50.954
Your husband...
Ex-husband.

03:50.990 --> 03:52.628
No, now, Carol,

03:52.660 --> 03:53.991
remember he's only
your ex-husband

03:54.030 --> 03:55.292
when you grant
a divorce.

03:55.330 --> 03:57.264
Otherwise, according
to Illinois law,

03:57.300 --> 03:58.597
he_has to wait
SIX months.

03:58.630 --> 04:00.359
That's my leverage.
That's your leverage, okay?

04:00.400 --> 04:02.265
(elevator bell dings)
Now, he wants to get
remarried right now,

04:02.310 --> 04:06.030
but he can only
do that if you
say, yes, okay?

04:06.070 --> 04:07.332
Excuse me.

04:07.380 --> 04:08.301
Alicia...

04:08.340 --> 04:10.342
Am I early?
No, I...

04:10.380 --> 04:13.543
What are you doing here?
You don't have to be here.

04:13.580 --> 04:15.741
I thought you were
taking the week off.

04:15.780 --> 04:18.248
No, I'm good. Ready to go.

04:19.720 --> 04:22.052
Cary, please, I'm ﬁne.

04:22.090 --> 04:25.423
Don't worry. I'm not gonna
fall apart on you.

04:25.460 --> 04:26.392
Let's go.

04:26.430 --> 04:28.352
Hello, Carol. How are you?

04:28.400 --> 04:29.560
I'm good, Asher.

04:29.600 --> 04:30.828
Wow, you're tan.

04:30.870 --> 04:31.894
I was in California.

04:31.930 --> 04:34.069
Oh! Huh, the book.

04:34.100 --> 04:35.465
How's it selling?

04:35.500 --> 04:37.604
Okay, that's enough
small talk for now.

04:37.640 --> 04:38.800
Alicia, Cary, welcome.

04:38.840 --> 04:40.068
Hello, Cary and Alicia.

04:40.110 --> 04:41.975
Excuse me a minute.

04:42.010 --> 04:44.570
Diane, what are you
doing here?

04:44.610 --> 04:46.373
Sitting in.
Why?

04:46.420 --> 04:49.446
Because I'm here.

04:49.490 --> 04:51.947
Okay, we would rather
this not be contentious,

04:51.990 --> 04:53.014
so we're willing
to compromise.

04:53.060 --> 04:56.450
Carol will grant Mr. Mercer's
request for a divorce.

04:56.490 --> 04:59.027
Mr. Mercer is not asking
for a divorce. He...

04:59.060 --> 05:00.698
We don't want this
to be contentious, either.

05:00.730 --> 05:04.962
Good. Then to answer Mr. Lee,
yes, your client did

05:05.000 --> 05:06.592
ask for a divorce
after sleeping with...

05:06.640 --> 05:08.335
ALICIA:
We_don't need to
go Into that here

05:08.370 --> 05:11.339
if we're all agreed
to our terms.

05:11.370 --> 05:12.906
A grant of divorce
in trade

05:12.940 --> 05:14.828
for leniency
on the postnuptials?

05:14.880 --> 05:16.973
Yes. So the only question
is custody.

05:17.010 --> 05:19.808
And since we all want
what's best for Nico,

05:19.850 --> 05:22.114
that would prove to be a simple
matter of visitation rights.

05:22.150 --> 05:25.347
Good! So basically,
we're done. Carol?

05:25.390 --> 05:27.779
If Asher agrees.
All I want is
for this to be over.

05:27.820 --> 05:30.618
Mr. Mercer, if you can
give me some wiggle room,
I can get...

05:30.660 --> 05:33.458
David, he's already
stated his preference.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.024
Yes, and I am offering
my opinion.

05:35.060 --> 05:36.664
Mr. Mercer?

05:36.700 --> 05:39.021
All I want is for
everybody to be happy.

05:39.070 --> 05:41.391
Good. Well, then
we have a deal.

05:41.440 --> 05:44.034
Except for custody.

05:44.070 --> 05:45.469
What the hell
was that?!

05:45.510 --> 05:46.579
That was called

05:46.610 --> 05:48.475
turning down
the temperature.

05:48.510 --> 05:50.148
You ought
to try it sometime.

05:50.180 --> 05:53.877
Diane, if this is about Will,

05:53.920 --> 05:57.014
you should take a break
and go on vacation.

05:57.050 --> 05:58.517
David, I have some advice
for you.

05:58.550 --> 06:00.450
Whenever you're tempted
to bring up Will's death

06:00.490 --> 06:03.027
and credit my behavior to it,
resist.

06:03.060 --> 06:06.154
Diane, I have
some advice for you.

06:06.190 --> 06:08.920
When in mourning,
don't make big decisions.

06:08.960 --> 06:12.123
At least for a year.

06:12.170 --> 06:14.536
Really?!

06:14.570 --> 06:16.435
Gretchen, move David Lee
out of his current office

06:16.470 --> 06:18.438
and into, um,
that office back there.

06:18.470 --> 06:19.630
You can't do that.
Yes, I can.

06:19.680 --> 06:22.103
I'm on the infrastructure
committee. Too bad you're not.

06:22.140 --> 06:25.075
Is that a big enough
decision for you?

06:29.790 --> 06:32.554
You know why she's doing
what she's doing?

06:32.590 --> 06:33.989
Why?

06:34.020 --> 06:37.524
I went to a bar
after Will's funeral.

06:37.560 --> 06:38.788
I wanted to be alone.

06:38.830 --> 06:41.697
I liked him.
I miss him.

06:41.730 --> 06:44.824
Why is she doing
what she's doing?

06:44.870 --> 06:47.691
And I happened to hear
two women talking
over a deal

06:47.740 --> 06:49.662
suggesting their
two firms merge.

06:49.710 --> 06:51.200
And do you know
what, David?

06:51.240 --> 06:53.606
Those two women
looked an awful
lot like Diane

06:53.640 --> 06:55.631
and Alicia Florrick.

06:55.680 --> 06:56.999
Is this true?

06:58.850 --> 07:02.047
She wants someone who will be
in her back pocket.

07:02.080 --> 07:04.617
So, we should do
something about it.

07:04.650 --> 07:06.083
CARY:
That was interesting.

07:06.120 --> 07:07.712
We got the result
we wanted.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.216
CAREY:
Cary, uh, do you
have a minute?

07:09.260 --> 07:11.080
Sure, what's up?

07:11.130 --> 07:15.226
CAREY:
Mr. Grant, this is Cary Agos.

07:15.260 --> 07:17.763
Mr. Grant's has a case, and
he's without representation.

07:17.800 --> 07:20.064
GRANT:
Yes, that's the problem.

07:20.100 --> 07:22.500
Lockhart/Gardner
won't take the case
for obvrous reasons.

07:22.540 --> 07:24.098
Because of Will?
Yes.

07:24.140 --> 07:26.973
Listen, I don't think
my son's responsible
for Will Gardner's death.

07:27.010 --> 07:28.602
Jeffrey was out
of his mind.

07:28.640 --> 07:30.642
The state's attorney's
office prosecuted him

07:30.680 --> 07:32.238
for a crime
he didn't commit.

07:32.280 --> 07:34.214
That's what forced him
to grab the gun.

07:34.250 --> 07:35.808
It's the state's attorney
that's at fault,

07:35.850 --> 07:37.078
and I'm gonna sue them.

07:37.120 --> 07:38.087
Sue them for?

07:38.120 --> 07:40.088
Wrongful prosecution.

07:40.120 --> 07:41.951
(gunshot)
CARY:
A wrongful prosecution suit

07:41.990 --> 07:43.457
is extremely hard to win.

07:43.490 --> 07:45.526
CAREY: Yes, except that he's
already had a meeting
with the state's attorney.

07:45.560 --> 07:46.652
GRANT:
Yes, he came to my house.

07:46.700 --> 07:47.894
CARY:
He came to you?

07:47.930 --> 07:49.591
Yes, Castro.

07:49.630 --> 07:50.528
He apologized.
He assured me

07:50.570 --> 07:52.561
that heads would roll
in his department.

07:52.600 --> 07:53.862
CAREY:
He wants this to be over.

07:53.900 --> 07:55.197
He wants
to clear the decks.

07:55.240 --> 07:59.267
Uh, Mr. Grant, you know
Alicia Florrick?

07:59.310 --> 08:01.574
Yes. Mrs. Florrick, hello.

08:01.610 --> 08:02.269
Hello.

08:02.310 --> 08:03.846
You were very nice to Jeffrey.

08:03.880 --> 08:06.041
CARY:
All right, so let's
take a step back

08:06.080 --> 08:07.775
and discuss the idea
of you filing suit.

08:07.820 --> 08:09.549
CAREY:
Cary's gorng to tell you

08:09.590 --> 08:11.649
there's a very high bar for
a wrongful prosecution...

08:11.690 --> 08:13.157
which is true.
What heads?

08:13.190 --> 08:15.511
What?

08:15.560 --> 08:18.882
You said Castro said,
"Heads would roll." Which heads?

08:18.930 --> 08:22.718
Well, he didn't say.
Is that important to the suit?

08:22.770 --> 08:24.692
CAREY:
No, we're just getting
more of a sense of the facts.

08:27.840 --> 08:30.536
Why? Why'd you ask that?

08:30.570 --> 08:32.629
We can't take this case.

08:32.680 --> 08:34.079
Because of Will?

08:35.580 --> 08:37.309
Oh, we... we have to listen.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.545
He'll just take the case
to someone else.

08:39.580 --> 08:43.243
Cary, listen to me. You take
this case, I quit the firm.

08:44.290 --> 08:47.179
I understand.

08:47.220 --> 08:48.551
I'll talk to him.

08:48.590 --> 08:50.979
I don't give a damn.

08:52.230 --> 08:54.596
Alicia, he's meeting
with the state's attorney.

08:54.630 --> 08:56.564
He told us that in confidence.
You cannot use It.

08:56.600 --> 08:59.125
Thank you, Cary.

08:59.170 --> 09:01.195
Yes, um, hello.
Can you put me through

09:01.240 --> 09:04.801
to a Finn Polmar's room.
I think he's in the ICU.

09:04.840 --> 09:07.673
He had the gunshot wound
to the shoulder.

09:07.710 --> 09:08.972
Mrs. Florrick, your appointment.

09:11.650 --> 09:15.609
Oh, I see. When? Thank you.

09:15.650 --> 09:19.245
Sondra, I need you to locate
the number of a Finn Polmar.

09:19.290 --> 09:21.986
He's the new ASA at the
state's attorney's office.

09:22.020 --> 09:23.624
He just got released
from the hospital.

09:23.660 --> 09:25.651
Sure. Do you want
me to connect you?

09:25.690 --> 09:27.590
Just let him know
I need to talk to him,

09:27.630 --> 09:28.722
and I'll be right back.

09:28.760 --> 09:30.091
PETER:
Well, the Sinclair Mission

09:30.130 --> 09:31.791
is exactly what families
in Illinois need.

09:31.830 --> 09:33.889
And I really have
to thank my wife

09:33.940 --> 09:35.259
for bringing it
to my attention.

09:35.300 --> 09:36.665
(camera shutters clicking)
My husband's being humble.

09:36.710 --> 09:38.837
It didn't need to be brought
to his attention.

09:38.870 --> 09:41.270
Well, we'll, uh,
we'll agree to disagree.

09:41.310 --> 09:43.369
At any rate,
if you'll excuse us,

09:43.410 --> 09:47.016
Alicia_and I have
to discuss our
son's SAT scores.

09:47.050 --> 09:49.314
(reporters laugh)
Thank you very much.

09:49.350 --> 09:51.318
MAN:
Can you stand back please.
Thank you.

09:51.350 --> 09:53.011
Are you all right?

09:53.060 --> 09:55.210
I'm here posing
with you for a photo op.

09:55.260 --> 09:56.625
Why wouldn't I be?

09:56.660 --> 09:58.685
Because of Will.

09:58.730 --> 10:02.689
I'm here for you, Peter.
What do you want from me?

10:02.730 --> 10:04.721
Well, I'd like
my wife back.

10:04.770 --> 10:05.828
I'm here.

10:05.870 --> 10:07.235
Are you?

10:07.270 --> 10:10.831
Oh, dear God, would everyone
just stop thinking

10:10.870 --> 10:13.179
I'm falling apart at
the friggin' seams?!

10:13.210 --> 10:14.802
Everyone?
When did I become everyone?

10:17.680 --> 10:20.649
(car door opens, closes)

10:20.680 --> 10:22.887
(phones ringing,
indistinct chatter nearby)

10:22.920 --> 10:26.310
Good. I think
we can handle
shared custody now.

10:26.350 --> 10:28.181
Nico is five years old,

10:28.220 --> 10:31.087
and we don't want to disrupt
his home life. Are we agreed?

10:31.130 --> 10:32.722
DAVID:
Hello.

10:32.760 --> 10:34.694
Hello, David, we're
almost settled here.

10:34.730 --> 10:35.856
Good.

10:35.900 --> 10:37.197
What nice offices, Cary.

10:37.230 --> 10:40.768
Very 19905 T-shirt factory.

10:40.800 --> 10:41.630
Thanks.
Where's Alicia?

10:41.670 --> 10:43.433
I thought she'd want
to be here for this.

10:43.470 --> 10:44.903
She'll be here in a minute.
What do you got?

10:44.940 --> 10:46.771
A nanny cam video.

10:46.810 --> 10:48.732
What nanny cam video?

10:48.780 --> 10:51.874
You and Asher agreed to have
installed in your house.

10:51.910 --> 10:53.138
(laughs)

10:53.180 --> 10:54.738
What's this about, Ash?

10:54.780 --> 10:55.849
Uh, David. We're decided.

10:58.150 --> 11:00.084
(passionate moaning)

11:00.120 --> 11:01.087
Oh, my God!

11:01.120 --> 11:02.849
You took that of me?!

11:02.890 --> 11:03.857
You were sleeping
with one of my students.

11:03.890 --> 11:04.857
What was I supposed to do?

11:04.890 --> 11:05.788
_You ran Off
With your nurse!

11:05.830 --> 11:07.923
I didn't run off.
What would you call it?!

11:07.960 --> 11:09.928
I'd call it grounds
for voiding your postnup.

11:09.970 --> 11:10.720
Infidelity.

11:10.770 --> 11:12.362
You're trying to
make me the villain?

11:12.400 --> 11:14.288
Maybe we should
settle this in court.

11:14.340 --> 11:16.331
(all talking over one another)

11:16.370 --> 11:18.201
Wait a minute!
You want to settle this,

11:18.240 --> 11:20.708
you don't want
this video shown in court,

11:20.740 --> 11:21.877
then take 20 cents
on the dollar.

11:21.910 --> 11:22.877
Like hell I will.

11:22.910 --> 11:24.844
Then we'll see you in court.

11:45.100 --> 11:46.169
DIANE:
KaHnda?

11:46.200 --> 11:48.430
I was just about to call you.

11:48.470 --> 11:50.165
I, um,

11:50.210 --> 11:51.734
I need a favor.

11:51.770 --> 11:52.976
Okay.

11:53.010 --> 11:55.774
I, uh, need you to go

11:55.810 --> 11:57.107
to Will's apartment.

11:57.150 --> 11:59.209
Okay.

11:59.250 --> 12:00.478
Why?

12:00.520 --> 12:02.408
I need to know how many
commitments we've made

12:02.450 --> 12:04.418
in New York and LA.

12:04.450 --> 12:07.010
His family boxed up
his work things.

12:07.060 --> 12:08.379
Bring them back here.

12:08.420 --> 12:10.957
Okay, I'll, uh,

12:10.990 --> 12:12.184
I'll head over.

12:15.230 --> 12:17.164
Diane?

12:17.200 --> 12:19.896
David Lee and Damian are trying

12:19.940 --> 12:22.909
to remove you
as managing partner.

12:24.470 --> 12:25.903
How do you know?

12:25.940 --> 12:27.237
I heard them talking.

12:27.280 --> 12:31.046
Without Will, they feel...

12:31.080 --> 12:33.139
you're unprotected.

12:35.350 --> 12:37.238
What do you want me to do?

12:37.290 --> 12:40.088
(huffs)

12:40.120 --> 12:42.315
(laughs):
I don't know.

12:42.360 --> 12:44.328
Well, you have to gather votes
to fight them.

12:44.360 --> 12:46.419
It'll never end, Kalinda.

12:46.460 --> 12:48.849
I can't fight them anymore.

12:48.900 --> 12:50.492
If they want to come after me,
let them...

12:50.530 --> 12:54.136
friggin' come after me.

12:55.240 --> 12:57.162
Well, let me see what I can do.

12:58.210 --> 13:00.098
What do you mean?

13:00.140 --> 13:03.075
Let me see
what I can do for you.

13:03.110 --> 13:05.271
Okay.

13:05.310 --> 13:07.312
Thanks, Kalinda.

13:10.050 --> 13:13.258
(door opens, closes)

13:13.290 --> 13:14.450
The postnup is clear.

13:14.490 --> 13:16.310
Any actual evidence
of infidelity

13:16.360 --> 13:18.419
by either spouse
invalidates the agreement.

13:18.460 --> 13:19.529
ALICIA:
Actual evidence

13:19.560 --> 13:21.152
means evidence you can admit.

13:21.200 --> 13:22.224
Like this footage
from Mrs. Mercer's

