I will hold him

27:13.830 --> 27:15.718
and love him

27:15.760 --> 27:17.057
and teach him.

27:17.100 --> 27:19.091
But to what end?

27:20.270 --> 27:21.396
Why?

27:28.710 --> 27:30.701
(gasping)

28:07.780 --> 28:09.077
Hey.

28:09.120 --> 28:11.714
(music shuts off)

28:15.190 --> 28:16.214
How's Grace?

28:16.260 --> 28:18.854
She's good.

28:18.890 --> 28:20.187
You're very brave out there.

28:20.230 --> 28:22.425
Thanks.
(giggles)

28:22.460 --> 28:24.724
I got arrested
at Wrigley Field.

28:24.770 --> 28:26.260
That was
pretty cool.

28:30.540 --> 28:32.360
I think I made a mistake.

28:32.410 --> 28:33.900
What mistake?

28:35.910 --> 28:38.799
Being a lavwer.

28:38.850 --> 28:42.741
You don't
like it?

28:42.780 --> 28:44.213
No.

28:44.250 --> 28:46.389
I don't know.
Sometimes I do.

28:46.420 --> 28:48.058
What would you do instead?

28:50.090 --> 28:52.081
I have no idea.

28:53.090 --> 28:54.853
I Wish I did.

28:54.900 --> 28:56.959
Do you want to dance with me?

28:59.070 --> 29:01.493
No.

29:04.940 --> 29:06.931
I think I'm going home now.

29:30.130 --> 29:32.098
ZACH:
Mom. Mom...

29:34.140 --> 29:36.461
Diane Lockhart's
on the phone.

29:36.500 --> 29:38.468
GRACE:
And you missed
a few other calls, too.

29:41.840 --> 29:43.068
Hello?

29:43.110 --> 29:45.271
I'm, uh, sorry to call you
at home, Alicia,

29:45.310 --> 29:46.971
but you weren't
picking up your cell

29:47.010 --> 29:48.819
and your office
didn't know where you were.

29:48.850 --> 29:50.010
It's okay.

29:50.050 --> 29:51.483
Um... things are moving

29:51.520 --> 29:54.887
quickly here, and I don't
want us to lose momentum.

29:54.920 --> 29:56.251
I just need to know if we're...

29:56.290 --> 29:58.121
if we're still talking merger.

29:58.160 --> 29:59.229
Can I call you back?

29:59.260 --> 30:00.227
Well, Alicia,

30:00.260 --> 30:01.352
if you're trying
to leverage this

30:01.400 --> 30:02.355
to get a better deal...

30:02.400 --> 30:04.391
No.

30:04.430 --> 30:06.125
I can't, uh...

30:08.270 --> 30:10.158
I'm a little under the weather.

30:10.200 --> 30:11.906
Let's talk when
I'm feeling better.

30:11.940 --> 30:13.168
Well, Alicia, can...

30:13.210 --> 30:15.201
(line clicks)

30:16.880 --> 30:17.869
Mom, are you okay?

30:17.910 --> 30:19.878
Yeah, you want us to get
you a NyQuil or something?

30:19.910 --> 30:21.047
I don't know.

30:21.080 --> 30:22.047
ZACH:
I'll get you a NyQuil.

30:22.080 --> 30:24.048
Could you make her tea?
Yeah.

30:24.090 --> 30:25.819
(footsteps receding)

30:40.170 --> 30:43.059
Well, very good.

30:43.100 --> 30:45.136
You know, this job is
like building track

30:45.170 --> 30:46.262
in front of a
bullet train.

30:46.310 --> 30:48.073
You ready?

30:48.110 --> 30:49.907
Yeah, absolutely.

30:49.940 --> 30:51.168
I'm sorry to drag you
through this.

30:51.210 --> 30:52.040
Yeah, no
problem.

30:52.080 --> 30:54.947
So I went back through
the Grant files,

30:54.980 --> 30:56.345
and I found a
bunch of e-mails

30:56.380 --> 30:58.348
about the professor,
Delaney,

30:58.390 --> 30:59.618
rejecting him
as a suspect.

30:59.650 --> 31:01.186
Uh, when was this?

31:01.220 --> 31:03.313
October.
Okay. Good.

31:03.360 --> 31:05.954
Uh, e-mails between
you and Geneva?

31:05.990 --> 31:07.150
No, between you and me.

31:07.190 --> 31:09.090
Really?

31:09.130 --> 31:10.392
Yeah.

31:10.430 --> 31:12.364
I guess you thought
Professor Delaney's alibi

31:12.400 --> 31:14.197
was a little bit dodgy,

31:14.240 --> 31:15.229
but then Jeffrey Grant's name
POPPEd UP

31:15.270 --> 31:18.000
and all those concerns
just disappeared, so...

31:18.040 --> 31:19.268
I'll have to go through
my records.

31:19.310 --> 31:21.232
Yeah.

31:21.280 --> 31:23.202
That's a good idea.

31:23.240 --> 31:25.470
You know what _
we're trying to do here, Finn?

31:25.510 --> 31:27.171
We're trying to bring
something to Chicago

31:27.210 --> 31:28.472
that it's never seen.

31:28.520 --> 31:31.182
A state's attorney's office
that is fair.

31:31.220 --> 31:35.156
Fair in prosecution,
investigation and sentencing.

31:36.160 --> 31:37.411
That's why I'm here.

31:37.460 --> 31:40.088
Good.

31:40.130 --> 31:41.950
One of these days,
I'm gonna need your help.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.649
With...
If I don't get elected

31:43.700 --> 31:46.362
next year, this office will go
right back to what it was.

31:47.370 --> 31:49.133
Yeah, okay.

31:49.170 --> 31:51.161
I'll talk to you.

32:03.750 --> 32:05.945
(groans softly)

32:20.430 --> 32:22.432
(phones ringing,
indistinct chatter nearby)

32:35.050 --> 32:36.972
To what do I owe the pleasure?

32:42.260 --> 32:44.421
What's this?
It's a copy

32:44.460 --> 32:46.189
of a retainer agreement
for a new client

32:46.230 --> 32:47.026
that Diane just signed.

32:47.060 --> 32:49.153
And she thinks
this will save her?

32:49.200 --> 32:50.349
I think she does.

32:50.400 --> 32:52.368
William Donnelly?

32:52.400 --> 32:55.198
Yeah. The Donnelly family

32:55.240 --> 32:57.765
has one of the big
import-export businesses

32:57.800 --> 33:00.064
in your old neighborhood.

33:00.110 --> 33:02.101
Diane really wanted
to represent them,

33:02.140 --> 33:04.608
so she offered them a discount
to come aboard.

33:04.650 --> 33:07.403
She...

33:07.450 --> 33:09.270
Come-come on board here?

33:09.320 --> 33:11.140
Mm-hmm. Lockhart/Gardner.

33:11.190 --> 33:13.283
Our newest client.

33:14.290 --> 33:15.484
She can't.

33:15.520 --> 33:16.612
It's done.

33:16.660 --> 33:18.651
A copy
of the retainer agreement

33:18.690 --> 33:21.250
is already in the mail
to a friend of yours.

33:21.300 --> 33:23.256
Liam Gerraghty?

33:23.300 --> 33:26.121
His organization has had
quite a few disagreements

33:26.170 --> 33:27.728
with Mr. Donnelly
over the years,

33:27.770 --> 33:31.501
all of which have been sorted
with some struggle.

33:31.540 --> 33:35.078
I wonder how Mr. Gerraghty
will view your firm

33:35.110 --> 33:36.634
representing his competition.

33:44.850 --> 33:47.444
So how did you find out
about me and the Gerraghtys?

33:47.490 --> 33:50.812
The copy was sent
by express mail, by the way.

33:50.860 --> 33:54.296
So unless you fancy
explaining yourself,

33:54.330 --> 33:57.049
you have about 18 hours
to quit the firm.

33:59.430 --> 34:01.534
Good-bye, Damian.

34:02.570 --> 34:06.028
(sighs)

34:08.280 --> 34:09.804
(sirens wailing,
indistinct radio transmission)

34:09.840 --> 34:12.400
MAN: People just think there
are black hats and white hats,

34:12.450 --> 34:16.409
but there are black hats
with white linings.

34:17.420 --> 34:20.082
White hats...

34:20.120 --> 34:23.578
with black linings.

34:23.620 --> 34:26.680
And there are hats that
change back and forth

34:26.730 --> 34:30.655
between white and black.

34:31.670 --> 34:33.194
And there are striped hats.

34:33.230 --> 34:35.232
Hey, Mom?

34:37.200 --> 34:40.465
Evil rests in the soul
of all men.
Hey.

34:40.510 --> 34:41.499
Do you want some dinner?

34:41.540 --> 34:43.201
I'm all right.

34:43.240 --> 34:44.571
You sure?

34:44.610 --> 34:45.872
You should probably
just eat something.

34:45.910 --> 34:48.117
It haunts them like ghosts
I will later.

34:48.150 --> 34:49.469
haunt a graveyard.

34:49.520 --> 34:52.239
And there is nothing you can do

34:52.290 --> 34:55.214
but curse God.

34:59.490 --> 35:01.458
CARY:
Thank you both

35:01.500 --> 35:02.626
for agreeing to sit down.

35:02.660 --> 35:04.469
DAVID: Make it quick;
I have work to do.

35:04.500 --> 35:05.626
Um, where's Alicia?

35:05.670 --> 35:07.126
Oh, she asked me
to step in for her.

35:07.170 --> 35:08.660
(sighs)
We're prepared

35:08.700 --> 35:10.292
to compromise on the
divorce settlement.

35:10.340 --> 35:11.364
We're not.

35:11.410 --> 35:12.809
David,

35:12.840 --> 35:14.705
both our clients
have been bloodied here,

35:14.740 --> 35:17.538
and there's no way to predict
which way the judge will go.

35:17.580 --> 35:19.605
Professor Mercer will honor
the terms of the postnup

35:19.650 --> 35:21.345
regarding child support
and alimony.

35:21.380 --> 35:23.245
In return, our client
will grant him a swift

35:23.280 --> 35:25.248
and uncontested divorce
so he can remarry.

35:25.290 --> 35:26.382
It's a win-win.

35:26.420 --> 35:28.217
Here's my counter.
No proceeds

35:28.260 --> 35:30.285
for the book,
no alimony,

35:30.320 --> 35:31.753
massive reduction
in child support,

35:31.790 --> 35:33.587
or you can get the hell
out of here.

35:33.630 --> 35:36.758
Your proposal is accepted, Cary.

35:36.800 --> 35:39.462
Diane, a word?

35:43.770 --> 35:45.499
I don't know what you
think you're doing.

35:45.540 --> 35:47.508
I'm making
an executive decision.

35:47.540 --> 35:49.303
I'm the ranking
partner here.

35:49.340 --> 35:51.171
Not for long; I have the votes.

35:51.210 --> 35:53.201
You had them.
You just lost one.

35:54.250 --> 35:55.547
What?

35:55.580 --> 35:56.911
You lost one vote.

35:56.950 --> 35:58.941
You'll have a hard time
finding your friend Damian

35:58.990 --> 36:00.787
for tomorrow's
partner meeting

36:00.820 --> 36:01.957
or any other one.

36:01.990 --> 36:04.288
You think I'm bluffing, hmm?

36:04.330 --> 36:05.479
Go. Check.

36:05.530 --> 36:07.657
You make a deal with Alicia,

36:07.690 --> 36:09.658
half the partners will rebel.
I make a deal

36:09.700 --> 36:11.918
with Alicia and bring
Chumhum back into the tent,

36:11.970 --> 36:13.562
half the partners
will be too busy

36:13.600 --> 36:15.898
counting their bonus money.

36:15.940 --> 36:18.363
You're no Will Gardner, Diane.

36:18.410 --> 36:20.469
You'll only hurt yourself
trying to be.

36:20.510 --> 36:21.602
(chuckles)

36:21.640 --> 36:23.574
Well, then fasten
your seat belts.

36:23.610 --> 36:25.771
We're heading for a lot of hurt.

36:37.420 --> 36:38.682
(tires squealing)

36:53.010 --> 36:54.773
(car door opens)

36:54.810 --> 36:57.438
(car door closes,
engine rewing)

36:57.480 --> 37:00.278
MAN (on TV):
Pigs in mud,

37:00.310 --> 37:01.311
that's all we are.

37:01.350 --> 37:02.612
(doorbell rings, door opens)

37:02.650 --> 37:03.912
God looks down on us

37:03.950 --> 37:05.611
and all he sees is mud
POLMAR: Sorry to bother you.

37:05.650 --> 37:08.448
_ and more mud. _
I just need to ask a question.

37:08.490 --> 37:09.912
(turns off TV)
I'm a client of your mom's.

37:09.960 --> 37:11.427
GRACE:
Oh, I'm sorry.

37:11.460 --> 37:12.654
She's really sick right now.

37:12.690 --> 37:14.658
Grace, it's okay.

37:14.700 --> 37:16.691
POLMAR:
Thank you.

37:18.530 --> 37:20.259
(clears throat)

37:23.800 --> 37:24.835
Hey.

37:24.870 --> 37:26.030
You okay?

37:26.070 --> 37:28.607
I'm so sorry. There's...

37:28.640 --> 37:30.733
no excuse for missing
your meeting.

37:30.780 --> 37:32.407
No, no, please.

37:32.450 --> 37:34.918
If you're... sick, you're sick.

37:34.950 --> 37:36.611
I should've called.

37:36.650 --> 37:38.789
No, it's okay.

37:40.090 --> 37:41.785
I just need to know,

37:41.820 --> 37:42.980
should I be hiring
another lavwer?

37:43.020 --> 37:44.282
No, no.

37:44.330 --> 37:46.651
I... Ijust...

37:46.690 --> 37:48.726
I needed a day.

37:48.760 --> 37:51.661
I just needed to sort
through a few things.

37:51.700 --> 37:53.429
I'll be well.

37:54.900 --> 37:57.460
Will really mattered to you.

38:01.940 --> 38:03.771
Yes.

38:03.810 --> 38:05.346
Look, um,

38:05.380 --> 38:07.371
uh...

38:10.520 --> 38:12.841
My wife and I lost a child

38:12.890 --> 38:14.881
in a miscarriage.

38:17.860 --> 38:19.680
It doesn't get solved quickly,

38:19.730 --> 38:22.699
and you can't just shake it off.

38:22.730 --> 38:26.689
So, if there's
anything I can do...

38:26.730 --> 38:28.834
Thanks.

38:28.870 --> 38:30.735
I mean, I know people
always say that,

38:30.770 --> 38:32.704
but, um,

38:32.740 --> 38:33.809
I mean it.

38:33.840 --> 38:36.502
I know you do.

38:36.540 --> 38:39.771
All right.

38:39.810 --> 38:41.812
I'll see you soon.

38:43.380 --> 38:44.813
(door opens)

38:45.790 --> 38:47.678
Hello.

38:47.720 --> 38:49.449
Hi.

38:49.490 --> 38:50.787
I'm Finn Polmar.

38:50.820 --> 38:51.787
Huh.

38:51.830 --> 38:53.024
I'm Peter Florrick.

38:53.060 --> 38:54.493
Yes, the governor, I know.

38:54.530 --> 38:55.599
I voted for you.

38:55.630 --> 38:57.393
That's good to know.

38:57.430 --> 38:58.522
Uh, your wife

38:58.570 --> 38:59.821
was just helping me with a case.

38:59.870 --> 39:01.792
Well, then you're
in great hands.

39:01.840 --> 39:04.434
Yeah. Yeah.

39:16.780 --> 39:18.782
(sniffles)

39:19.750 --> 39:21.115
You okay?

39:21.150 --> 39:22.879
I really wish everyone
would stop asking me that.

39:22.920 --> 39:23.989
I'm fine.

39:24.020 --> 39:25.885
Oh.

39:25.930 --> 39:29.388
You missed the Founders' Dinner.

39:29.430 --> 39:31.898
I just was worried
about you.

39:31.930 --> 39:33.158
Sorry.

39:33.200 --> 39:35.896
I don't often ask you to come
to these, uh, political events.

39:35.940 --> 39:37.828
I'll go to the next one.

39:38.870 --> 39:40.804
Alicia,

39:40.840 --> 39:43.809
the way you're handling
this Will thing...

39:43.840 --> 39:45.501
I'm doing...

39:45.550 --> 39:46.505
my best.

39:46.550 --> 39:48.541
Oh, well, if this is your best,

39:48.580 --> 39:49.979
then I think we need to talk.

39:55.120 --> 39:57.111
Look, you lost a friend.

39:58.890 --> 40:01.188
You didn't lose your child;
you didn't lose your husband.

40:01.230 --> 40:04.529
I lost my husband
a long time ago.

40:04.570 --> 40:07.130
Oh, my...

40:07.170 --> 40:10.560
You cannot go back there.

40:10.600 --> 40:11.828
I don't have to.

40:11.870 --> 40:14.134
I'm still living it every day.

40:14.170 --> 40:15.603
(under breath):
Oh, my God.

40:15.640 --> 40:19.098
How many times
do I have to tell you?

40:19.150 --> 40:21.641
When I cheated,
it didn't mean anything.

40:21.680 --> 40:23.045
Well, then that was a waste,

40:23.080 --> 40:25.617
because when I cheated,
it did!

40:25.650 --> 40:28.619
Well, I can't compete
with a dead man,

40:28.660 --> 40:29.809
but if you think your life

40:29.860 --> 40:31.487
would've been better with Will,
you are kidding yourself.

40:31.530 --> 40:33.521
Stop it, Peter!
No, I'm not gonna

40:33.560 --> 40:34.959
let you throw away
this marriage

40:35.000 --> 40:36.820
because you have some
idealized notion

40:36.860 --> 40:39.169
of a man who you're not
even sure cared about you!

40:39.200 --> 40:40.462
You're a bastard.

40:40.500 --> 40:41.535
And you're a selfish bitch,

40:41.570 --> 40:43.231
but you know what?!

40:43.270 --> 40:45.500
We're all that we have.

40:49.940 --> 40:52.670
(sighs)

40:58.920 --> 41:01.559
No.

41:01.590 --> 41:03.581
Not anymore.

41:09.060 --> 41:10.550
Don't worry;
I'm not gonna divorce you.

41:10.600 --> 41:12.693
You're to valuable
to me profe55ionally,

41:12.730 --> 41:13.867
just like I am to you.

41:13.900 --> 41:16.630
But we're not gonna see
each other anymore.

41:16.670 --> 41:19.059
Not unless we have to.

41:19.110 --> 41:20.964
If you need me
at a political event,

41:21.010 --> 41:22.500
you call the office.

41:22.540 --> 41:23.939
My assistant will put it
on my calendar.

41:23.980 --> 41:25.641
Really?

41:25.680 --> 41:26.749
I'm not finished.

41:26.780 --> 41:28.919
You are free...

41:28.950 --> 41:31.646
to see and sleep
with whomever you like,

41:31.690 --> 41:33.089
but I don't want to know,

41:33.120 --> 41:35.554
and under no circumstances

41:35.590 --> 41:37.717
are our children to know.

41:37.760 --> 41:39.751
Understood?

41:43.730 --> 41:45.891
Is this because you want
to sleep with someone else?

41:45.930 --> 41:48.125
Get out of my house, Peter.

41:48.170 --> 41:50.695
Get...

42:05.150 --> 42:08.586
This is David Lee
at Lockhart/Gardner.

42:08.620 --> 42:11.157
Do you have a minute? Uh-huh.

42:11.190 --> 42:13.727
What do you think
about a merger?

42:13.760 --> 42:16.058
What do I think?

42:16.100 --> 42:17.727
I think...

42:17.760 --> 42:18.829
that sounds interesting.

